{
  "stem": "22869.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Meant the world to me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the fact that I saw my name in print, that somebody in the world knows that Manny Mittelman is locked up in Auschwitz, meant to me much more than the two cans of the sardines, of course.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So in other words, it gives you a ray of hope.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Wait a minute-- somebody may be working in your behalf.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The world knows.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You have a chance, maybe, maybe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very little.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We knew from seeping in-- as I mentioned to you before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were always some civilians coming into the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we knew some kinds of-- let's see, it was the end of 1944 in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We could hear, already, shooting.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't know what it was until, through rumors, we find out the Russians are coming, and they're so close already.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We knew that Germany's on-- on the verge of-- not complete collapse, but we knew that they were being surrounded, from the little rumors that came in through the civilians.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know-- you see this through a sieve.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were, of course, looking forward to a liberation, but we were also more scared that there would never be a liberation because nobody, in our minds, nobody ever believed they would let us come out and be live witnesses to tell the world.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we get into the next segment about leaving Birkenau, you'll find out the reason why we acted the way we did act.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because every person judges the people who are trying to torture you by their previous experiences.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And by the previous experiences, you knew that a German does not want a Jew to come out in the world alive to be able to tell this story.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was their main purpose.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "For some reason, they were afraid.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
